# Atlassian MCP Server Routing

- The `user-renaissance-atlassian` MCP server requires OAuth auth that consistently fails. Do NOT use it.
- Use `plugin-engineer-buddy-renaissance-atlassian` for all Jira and Confluence operations. It has the full tool set (`getJiraIssue`, `editJiraIssue`, `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql`, `getConfluencePage`, etc.) and works without a separate auth step.
- CloudId for the illuminate site: `6b6fffef-32f8-44d1-82ea-ad3773ab29c8`. You can also call `getAccessibleAtlassianResources` to retrieve it.
- When editing Jira issue descriptions, use `contentFormat: "markdown"` and `responseContentFormat: "markdown"` for readability.
